body.name: Luminary Global Tactical Trauma Kit Fully Stocked First Aid Kit Backpack EMS/EMT First Responder Medical Bug Out Bag for Preppers Professionals and Outdoorsman (Olive Drab)
features: ✅ Luminary is Veteran-Owned & Operated - FULL KIT CONTENTS LISTED IN DESCRIPTION BELOW - fully stocked with over 200 medical supplies

✅ The tactical backpack has 4 compartments (2 Main -2 Secondary) with mesh pockets designed to easily organize your gear for quick access with plenty of room to add additional items. With 6 cinch straps (4 on sides, 2 on bottom) you can compress and secure your entire load

✅ The top pouch is perfect for storing personal items such as sunglasses, cell phones, or keys with a designated area for a nameplate or moral patch. The top handle is adjustable to accommodate any style of carry.

✅ The back panel is breathable and ventilated (moisture-wicking) keeping you cool and the sweat at bay on long hauls while the waist strap keeps the pack secure to your body to avoid unneeded rubbing.

✅ MOLLE platforms located on the front, sides, and shoulder straps to easily add pouches, IFAK, tools, and accessories. The cushioned shoulder straps designed for comfort when carrying heavy loads to evenly distribute weight and have D-Rings for additional functionality.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: The Luminary Tactical Trauma Kit is fully stocked with over 200 medical supplies preparing you for any situation. Expect the Unexpected – Be Prepared Luminary Global is a Service-Disabled Veteran-Owned Small Business, Owned and operated by a retired U.S. Army First Sergeant. At Luminary, our mission is simple, to provide Emergency Medical Service (EMS), Fire, Law Enforcement, Military, and Citizens with the equipment and supplies they need to save lives at home and abroad. This medical Go Bag is ideal for Professionals, Preppers, Outdoor Enthusiasts, and Citizens alike. Ideal for EDC Everyday Carry, Natural Disasters (Hurricanes, Tornados, etc.), Hunting, Hiking, Camping, or family road trips. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Purchased to put in my food prep and storage
reviews.reviewText: The kit is well made, it's sturdy and the zippers are made of high-quality material that isn't going to break over time or quickly. I purchased it to put in my food storage as a first aid kit, in case it is ever needed. It's got everything you'll ever need and more. I am very happy with this first aid kit. It is a bulky one because it comes with so much, but I would prefer knowing I have everything I will ever need than be missing something in my time of need. It would fit well in the back of a car, closet, or storage, but it's not one I would take backpacking because it's so large. I might use it to replenish my backpacking first aid kit though if needed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This is great to have for groups or major travel in case there is a major emergency. I do think it would help by adding more basic bandages, maybe an oximeter would also be handy with the blood pressure cuff.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Awesome kit and great price
reviews.reviewText: This is a very wonderful first aid kit for the money. I have bought a few of these over the years for different boats.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 5, 2021
reviews.reviewText: As an EMT I wanted a go bag for my truck. Only thing I wanted in this kit was a blood glucose meter.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 14, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Looks like a good starter kit to build off of. I suppose it would help in an emergency with what they send you.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 15, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This kit is well worth the value.
reviews.reviewText: I am a former EMT/Paramedic. I purchased this kit because I was assisting with our local RACES of which I’m a member at the Baker to Vegas run. I’m glad I had it with me because one of our runners was extremely dehydrated to the point of heat stroke when he finished his leg of the rest. I used the to ice packs to cool him down by placing them around his neck. He was also given fluids and he recovered after about 30 min.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 17, 2023
Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best bag we have ever had
reviews.reviewText: The ultimate med pack! Came with everything we need in the event of a big out. We added some IV and saline bags and things but this has it all. We have recommended everyone to get this bag. Even if you aren’t into survival this is a great bag to have in your car, in the house. It’s packed with everything!
